duties_responsibilities.duty: Provide obstetric and gynecologic care, including prenatal care and surgical procedures, in a locum tenens capacity.
Participate in hospital call schedule, assisting with patient care and emergencies as needed.
Manage patient case load, ensuring quality care and effective treatment plans.
Collaborate with support staff and medical professionals to deliver comprehensive and compassionate care to patients.
Maintain accurate medical records and documentation, adhering to best practices and regulatory requirements.

education_certification.credential: Board Certification in Obstetrics and Gynecology
